I&rsquo;ve made a dendrogram based off the chemical lists provided by NHS digital. (As part of their CCG Spending data).
These lists give a name, and lookup code for every drug licensed in the UK based on BNF Sections. E.g Adenosine (Chemical Sub: 0203020C0), i.e BNF &gt; 2. &lsquo;Cardiovascular System&rsquo; &gt; 2.3 &lsquo;Anti-Arrhythmic Drugs&rsquo; &gt; 2.3.2 &lsquo;Drugs for Arrhythmias&rsquo;
This 3-layer dendrogram is composed of every drug listed on this look-up for potential NHS spending.
